        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat: per-channel thread.requireExplicitMention override for Slack",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Add per-channel `thread.requireExplicitMention` override for Slack.\n- Preserve current Slack channel controls while rebasing onto current `main`: `allowBots: \"mentions\"` and `botLoopProtection` remain intact.\n- Remove the unrelated dependency-contract relaxation from this PR scope.\n\n## Use Case\n\nAn operator wants some Slack channels, such as client-facing channels, to require `@bot` on every thread reply while internal channels keep the default \"mention once, then auto-participate\" behavior.\n\n## Changes\n\n**`src/config/zod-schema.providers-core.ts`**\n- Add channel-level `thread.requireExplicitMention` via `SlackChannelThreadSchema`.\n- Keep `allowBots: boolean | \"mentions\"` and `botLoopProtection` on `SlackChannelSchema`.\n\n**`extensions/slack/src/monitor/channel-config.ts`**\n- Add `threadRequireExplicitMention` to resolved channel config.\n- Resolve with fallback order: channel entry -> wildcard entry -> account default.\n\n**`extensions/slack/src/monitor/message-handler/prepare.ts`**\n- Pass the account default into channel config resolution.\n- Use the effective channel policy before collecting implicit thread mentions.\n- Use the same effective channel policy for activation gating.\n\n**`extensions/slack/src/monitor/auth.ts` / `slash.ts` / `context.ts`**\n- Thread policy resolution uses the same account-default fallback path.\n\n**Tests / generated docs**\n- Add coverage for channel override true and false.\n- Regenerate bundled channel config metadata and config docs baseline.\n\n## Config Example\n\n```json\n{\n  \"channels\": {\n    \"slack\": {\n      \"accounts\": {\n        \"mybot\": {\n          \"thread\": { \"requireExplicitMention\": false },\n          \"channels\": {\n            \"C0CLIENT01\": {\n              \"enabled\": true,\n              \"requireMention\": true,\n              \"thread\": { \"requireExplicitMention\": true }\n            },\n            \"C0INTERNAL01\": {\n              \"enabled\": true,\n              \"requireMention\": true,\n              \"thread\": { \"requireExplicitMention\": false }\n            }\n          }\n        }\n      }\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n## Test plan\n\n- [x] Rebased onto current `main`; exact head `f12c44e48e9c1b837aae194a0af7773b159a2838`.\n- [x] `node scripts/run-tsgo.mjs -p tsconfig.plugin-sdk.dts.json --declaration true && node --experimental-strip-types scripts/write-plugin-sdk-entry-dts.ts`\n- [x] `pnpm config:channels:check`\n- [x] `pnpm config:docs:check`\n- [x] `pnpm exec vitest run extensions/slack/src/monitor/message-handler/prepare.test.ts extensions/slack/src/monitor/monitor.test.ts` - 2 files / 109 tests passed\n- [x] `pnpm exec oxfmt --check CHANGELOG.md docs/channels/slack.md extensions/slack/src/monitor/auth.ts extensions/slack/src/monitor/channel-config.ts extensions/slack/src/monitor/context.ts extensions/slack/src/monitor/message-handler/prepare.test.ts extensions/slack/src/monitor/message-handler/prepare.ts extensions/slack/src/monitor/monitor.test.ts extensions/slack/src/monitor/slash.ts src/config/types.slack.ts src/config/zod-schema.providers-core.ts`\n- [x] `pnpm lint --threads=8` inspected. It currently fails on latest `main` in `extensions/openrouter/provider-routing.ts`; this PR does not modify that file.\n- [ ] Maintainer-run Mantis Slack desktop smoke or equivalent live Slack proof, if maintainers require browser-visible transport evidence before merge.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n- Behavior or issue addressed: Per-channel Slack `thread.requireExplicitMention` now overrides the account-level default for both early implicit-thread mention collection and later activation gating, while preserving current `allowBots: \"mentions\"` and `botLoopProtection` behavior.\n- Real environment tested: Local OpenClaw source checkout at `/Users/shannon/repos/openclaw` on macOS Darwin arm64, Node v22.22.2, pnpm v11.1.0; branch `feat/slack-channel-thread-mention-override-rebased`, exact head `f12c44e48e9c1b837aae194a0af7773b159a2838`.\n- Exact steps or command run after this patch: Replayed the Slack monitor preparation path with focused Slack monitor suites and regenerated/checked config surfaces:\n  ```text\n  node scripts/run-tsgo.mjs -p tsconfig.plugin-sdk.dts.json --declaration true && node --experimental-strip-types scripts/write-plugin-sdk-entry-dts.ts\n  pnpm config:channels:check\n  pnpm config:docs:check\n  pnpm exec vitest run extensions/slack/src/monitor/message-handler/prepare.test.ts extensions/slack/src/monitor/monitor.test.ts\n  pnpm exec oxfmt --check CHANGELOG.md docs/channels/slack.md extensions/slack/src/monitor/auth.ts extensions/slack/src/monitor/channel-config.ts extensions/slack/src/monitor/context.ts extensions/slack/src/monitor/message-handler/prepare.test.ts extensions/slack/src/monitor/message-handler/prepare.ts extensions/slack/src/monitor/monitor.test.ts extensions/slack/src/monitor/slash.ts src/config/types.slack.ts src/config/zod-schema.providers-core.ts\n  pnpm lint --threads=8\n  ```\n- Evidence after fix: Redacted terminal output from the real source checkout:\n  ```text\n  $ node scripts/run-tsgo.mjs -p tsconfig.plugin-sdk.dts.json --declaration true && node --experimental-strip-types scripts/write-plugin-sdk-entry-dts.ts\n  exit_code=0\n\n  $ pnpm config:channels:check\n  $ node --import tsx scripts/generate-bundled-channel-config-metadata.ts --check\n  exit_code=0\n\n  $ pnpm config:docs:check\n  $ node --import tsx scripts/generate-config-doc-baseline.ts --check\n  OK docs/.generated/config-baseline.sha256\n\n  $ pnpm exec vitest run extensions/slack/src/monitor/message-handler/prepare.test.ts extensions/slack/src/monitor/monitor.test.ts\n  Test Files  2 passed (2)\n  Tests  109 passed (109)\n  Duration  5.78s\n\n  $ pnpm exec oxfmt --check ...\n  All matched files use the correct format.\n  Finished in 1640ms on 11 files using 10 threads.\n\n  $ pnpm lint --threads=8\n  Fails on latest main in extensions/openrouter/provider-routing.ts:\n  unicorn(no-useless-fallback-in-spread): Empty fallbacks in spreads are unnecessary\n  PR diff against origin/main does not include extensions/openrouter/provider-routing.ts.\n  ```\n- Observed result after fix: The current PR head is `MERGEABLE`; the focused Slack monitor suites pass both override directions, including channel override true suppressing unmentioned thread replies and channel override false allowing implicit thread participation under an account default of true.\n- What was not tested: No production Slack Gateway or installed OpenClaw runtime was modified. Browser-visible Slack desktop proof is left to the trusted Mantis Slack desktop workflow because it requires maintainer-level workflow dispatch and secret-bearing QA infrastructure.\n",
